article.description: Jessica Lindstrom scored 22 points and grabbed 13 rebounds and No. 23 Green Bay used a 28-3 run in the second half to roll to an 81-48 win over Oakland on Saturday for its sixth-straight win.
article.headline: No. 23 Green Bay women use big run to top Oakland 81-48
article.linkText: No. 23 Green Bay women use big run to top Oakland 81-48
article.story:
ROCHESTER, Mich. --  Jessica Lindstrom scored 22 points and grabbed 13 rebounds and No. 23 Green Bay used a 28-3 run in the second half to roll to an 81-48 win over Oakland on Saturday for its sixth-straight win.

Allie LeClaire added 12 points for the Phoenix (17-2, 7-1 Horizon League).

Green Bay led 36-26 at the half and was up 39-29 when LeClaire made a layup. That started a run of eight straight points before Taylor Jones scored for Oakland, followed by eight more before a Jones free throw. The Phoenix scored the last five points of the third quarter and the first seven of the fourth quarter for a 65-32 lead with 7:13 remaining.

In that 8 1/2 minutes, Green Bay went 10 for 12 while the Grizzlies (10-9, 3-5) were 1 for 11.

The Phoenix finished 11 of 20 from distance and shot 59 percent overall to 28 percent for Oakland.

Sha'Keya Graves had 16 points for Oakland.
